be%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELiquor%20licenses%20for%20two%20of%20Trump's%20NJ%20golf%20courses%20remain%20under%20review%20due%20to%20his%20felony%20conviction.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20state%20officials%20said%20they%20have%20extended%20the%20two%20licenses%20for%20another%20six%20months.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20can't%20touch%20any%20liquor-sale%20proceeds%20for%20the%20clubs%20at%20Colts%20Neck%20and%20Bedminster%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Champagne%20will%20keep%20flowing%20for%20another%20six%20months%20at%20two%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20New%20Jersey%20golf%20courses%2C%20despite%20his%20felony%20conviction.%20For%20now%2C%20though%2C%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20is%20barred%20from%20touching%20the%20proceeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20with%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Attorney%20General's%20Office%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20they%20have%20issued%20temporary%2C%20half-year%20extensions%20for%20the%20liquor%20licenses%20at%20the%20Trump%20National%20Golf%20Club%20in%20Colts%20Neck%20and%20the%20Trump%20National%20Golf%20Club%20in%20Bedminster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last-minute%20extensions%20were%20necessary%20to%20keep%20the%20drinks%20flowing%20while%20state%20officials%20continue%20to%20review%20Trump's%20application%20to%20renew%20the%20licenses%20for%20the%20coming%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20extension%2C%20the%20licenses%20at%20the%20Colts%20Neck%20and%20Bedminster%20clubs%20would%20have%20expired%20outright%20on%20Monday%2C%20June%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20extensions%20come%20with%20heavy%20strings%20attached%20%E2%80%94%20including%20that%20Trump%2C%20as%20a%20convicted%20felon%2C%20and%20any%20other%20corporate%20members%20of%20the%20clubs'%20LLCs%20must%20keep%20their%20hands%20out%20of%20the%20bar%20tills%20at%20the%20two%20clubs%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorney%20general's%20Division%20of%20Alcoholic%20Beverage%20Control%20is%20requiring%20that%20proceeds%20from%20the%20two%20clubs'%20liquor%20licenses%20be%20held%20in%20untouched%20accounts%20kept%20separate%20from%20those%20for%20the%20clubs'%20other%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20constraint%20that%20Peter%20Rhodes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lawyer%20who's%20specialized%20for%2030%20years%20in%20New%20Jersey%20liquor%20licensing%20%E2%80%94%20says%20he's%20never%20seen%20imposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20when%20a%20license%20owner%20or%20beneficiary%20becomes%20a%20felon%2C%20they%20are%20simply%20given%20time%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20the%20license%2C%20Rhodes%20said%2C%20usually%20by%20selling%20or%20transferring%20their%20interest%20to%20a%20non-felon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20might%20infer%20that%20the%20ABC%20is%20struggling%20with%20how%20to%20handle%20this%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20with%20how%20to%20deprive%20a%20felon%20of%20the%20proceeds%20of%20their%20license%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20I%20find%20it%20peculiar%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rhodes%2C%20whose%20Haddonfield-based%20firm%2C%20Cahill%2C%20Wilinski%2C%20Rhodes%20%26amp%3B%20Joyce%2C%20has%20served%20for%2050%20years%20as%20counsel%20to%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Licensed%20Beverage%20Association.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20don't%20say%20is%20what%20happens%20to%20that%20money%20if%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20they%20find%20that%20he%20is%20disqualified%2C%26quot%3B%20Rhodes%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can't%20just%20confiscate%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20New%20Jersey%20Attorney%20General%20Matt%20Platkin%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20special%20conditions%20%26quot%3Bare%20consistent%20with%20the%20division's%20obligation%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20liquor%20licensees%20comply%20with%20the%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNew%20Jersey%20statutes%20state%20that%20profiting%20from%20a%20liquor%20license%20is%20a%20privilege%2C%20not%20a%20right%20granted%20by%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20soon%20after%20Trump's%20May%2030%2C%202024%2C%20conviction%20that%20New%20Jersey%20officials%20first%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-loophole-may-protect-trump-liquor-licenses-despite-his-felonies-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20two%20golf%20club%20licenses%20were%20under%20review%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%20of%202024%2C%20they%20announced%20that%20they%20did%20not%20intend%20to%20renew%20the%20licenses%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnj-pull-trump-golf-liquor-licenses-for-hush-money-felonies-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump's%20new%20status%20as%20a%20felon.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Bedminster%20and%20Colts%20Neck%20licenses%20are%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Jr.%2C%20the%20president's%20son%2C%20but%20the%20state%20AG's%20office%20ruled%20at%20the%20time%20that%20Trump%20himself%20is%20the%20primary%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20clubs'%20liquor%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20license-revocation%20hearing%20%E2%80%94%20at%20which%20Trump%20would%20bear%20the%20burden%20of%20proving%20he%20was%20qualified%20to%20be%20a%20license%20beneficiary%20%E2%80%94%20was%20initially%20set%20for%20July%202024%2C%20only%20to%20be%20repeatedly%20canceled.%20A%20new%20hearing%20date%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Jersey%20law%20requires%20liquor%20licenses%20be%20revoked%20if%20their%20owner%20or%20primary%20beneficiary%20is%20sentenced%20for%20a%20crime%20of%20moral%20turpitude%2C%20a%20category%20which%20includes%20felony%20falsifying%20business%20records.%20That's%20the%20state%20charge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-next-steps-liquor-licenses-criminal-appeal-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump%20was%20sentenced%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20in%20Manhattan%20in%20January%2C%20nine%20days%20before%20his%20inauguration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week's%20license%20extension%20further%20requires%20that%20by%20September%2030%2C%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20provide%20the%20alcoholic%20beverage%20control%20officials%20with%20details%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20corporate%20structure%2C%20ownership%2C%20and%20beneficiary%20interests%26quot%3B%20behind%20the%20licenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20third%20New%20Jersey%20golf%20club%20is%20the%20Trump%20National%20Golf%20Club%20Philadelphia%2C%20which%20is%2045%20minutes%20from%20that%20city%20in%20Pine%20Hill.%20The%20town%2C%20not%20the%20state%2C%20regulates%20that%20license%2C%20which%20was%20also%20due%20to%20expire%20June%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20Pine%20Hill%20and%20a%20food%20and%20beverage%20manager%20at%20the%20golf%20club%20there%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20legal%20officer%20of%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20also%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20license%20renewals%20and%20the%20required%20special%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25987156-trump-bedminster-colts-neck-tap-20250630%2F%3Fembed%3D1%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-nj-golf-clubs-can-serve-liquor-despite-felonies-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751406896000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686420d23d5881a51c1c764a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-nj-golf-clubs-can-serve-liquor-despite-felonies-2025