%20as%20Typhon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20system's%20presence%20in%20the%20region%20deeply%20annoyed%20Beijing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETroops%20deployed%20to%20the%20Pacific%20tinkered%20with%20and%20reworked%20a%20missile%20system%20in%20the%20field%2C%20showing%20the%20value%20of%20soldier-driven%20design%20input%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-new-us-missile-system-keeps-upsetting-china-mrc-typon-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeployment%20that%20irritated%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20recent%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoldiers%20were%20in%20the%20Philippines%20and%20working%20with%20the%20US%20Army's%20new%20Mid-Range%20Capability%2C%20or%20Typhon%2C%20missile%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%2C%20a%20watchdog%20agency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-25-107263%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20%3C%2Fa%3Elast%20month%20on%20the%20Army's%20modernization%20efforts%20for%20its%20artillery%2C%20rocket%2C%20and%20missile%20systems.%20Citing%20conversations%20with%20the%20program's%20officials%2C%20the%20GAO%20said%20that%20there%20were%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20design%20changes%26quot%3B%20made%20%26quot%3Bduring%20development%20based%20on%20user%20input%20provided%20during%20new%20equipment%20training%20and%20other%20exercises.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20improvements%20made%20included%20reducing%20the%20reload%20time%20and%20stress%20on%20the%20system's%20components%2C%20and%20they%20were%20made%20by%20soldiers%20on%20the%20ground%20during%20those%20exercises.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20because%20of%20the%20orientation%20of%20the%20launcher%2C%20soldiers%20suggested%20moving%20certain%20access%20points%20and%20panel%20connections%20on%20the%20trailer%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20reload%2C%20operate%2C%20and%20maintain%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUser%20input%20on%20the%20system%20was%20collected%20during%20and%20after%20its%20deployment%20to%20the%20Philippines%20last%20year%20as%20part%20of%20a%20joint%20US-Philippine%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usarpac.army.mil%2FOur-Story%2FOur-News%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3740807%2Fus-armys-mid-range-capability-makes-its-first-deployment-in-the-philippines-for%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20statement%20at%20the%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20US%20Army%20Pacific%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Blandmark%20deployment%26quot%3B%20marking%20%26quot%3Ba%20significant%20milestone%20for%20the%20new%20capability%20while%20enhancing%20interoperability%2C%20readiness%2C%20and%20defense%20capabilities%20in%20coordination%20with%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20of%20the%20Philippines.%26quot%3B%20It%20marked%20the%20system's%20first%20overseas%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221266%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20missile%20is%20fired%20from%20a%20launcher%20in%20a%20desert%20landscape%20with%20grey%20clouds%20across%20a%20blue%20sky%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68641799f748d8c055f4bcbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22949%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMRC%20has%20been%20test-fired%20in%20the%20US%20and%20is%20one%20of%20the%20Army's%20new%20systems%20designed%20to%20fill%20capability%20gaps.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20photo%20of%20the%20Mid-Range%20Capability%20Project%20Office%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MRC%20is%20one%20of%20the%20Army's%20newest%20missile%20systems.%20It's%20a%20versatile%20ground-based%20missile%20system%20capable%20of%20firing%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-aircraft-spotted-sm6-missile-newly-tested-in-combat-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Standard%20Missile%206%20(SM-6)%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-submarines-getting-ship-killer-missile-able-to-counter-china-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETomahawk%20Land%20Attack%20Missile%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20designed%20to%20fill%20a%20key%20gap%20in%20the%20US%20arsenal%20in%20terms%20of%20range%20and%20flexibility.%20While%20it%20wasn't%20fired%20during%20the%20trainings%2C%20its%20presence%20angered%20China%2C%20which%20demanded%20it%20be%20removed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202024%2C%20Lin%20Jian%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20China's%20foreign%20ministry%2C%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Feng%2Fxw%2Ffyrbt%2Flxjzh%2F202409%2Ft20240919_11493204.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20made%20its%20opposition%20to%20the%20deployment%20clear%20more%20than%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20deployment%20is%20a%20move%20to%20turn%20back%20the%20wheel%20of%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20gravely%20threatens%20regional%20countries'%20security%2C%20incites%20geopolitical%20confrontation%2C%20and%20has%20aroused%20high%20vigilance%20and%20concerns%20of%20countries%20in%20the%20region.%26quot%3B%20China%20notably%20maintains%20a%20large%20arsenal%20of%20ballistic%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20also%20expressed%20its%20frustrations%20to%20the%20Philippines.%20In%20August%20last%20year%2C%20Philippine%20Foreign%20Secretary%20Enrique%20Manalo%20said%20his%20Chinese%20counterpart%2C%20Wang%20Yi%2C%20had%20expressed%20concerns%20the%20weapon%20could%20destabilize%20the%20security%20and%20relations%20of%20the%20region%2C%20and%20that%20when%20they%20discussed%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-got-dramatic-over-us-missile-system-in-pacific-ally-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina%20%26quot%3Bmade%20it%20very%20dramatic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20said%20the%20Philippines%2C%20a%20key%20US%20ally%2C%20is%20serving%20American%20interests%20ot%20the%20detriment%20of%20its%20own%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20China%20has%20kept%20up%20its%20complaints%20amid%20reports%20of%20a%20coming%20second%20MRC%20deployment%20to%20the%20Philippines%2C%20which%20has%20expressed%20great%20interest%20in%20the%20system's%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MRC's%20development%20came%20after%20the%202019%20US%20withdrawal%20from%20the%201987%20Intermediate-Range%20Nuclear%20Forces%20Treaty%2C%20which%20banned%20nuclear%20and%20conventional%20ground-launched%20ballistic%20and%20cruise%20missiles%20with%20ranges%20of%20500%20to%205%2C500%20kilometers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Four%20of%20the%20US%20Army's%20Mid-Range%20Capability%20missile%20systems%2C%20which%20are%20mounted%20on%20trucks%2C%20are%20parked%20in%20a%20formation%20on%20a%20dirt%20ground%20with%20trees%20and%20a%20grey%20sky%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f41e97ce3009a0fac952d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222318%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20and%20Japanese%20officials%20have%20also%20discussed%20deploying%20an%20MRC%20system%20to%20Japan.%3Cp%3EDarrell%20Ames%2FExecutive%20Office%20Missiles%20and%20Space%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20withdrawal%2C%20which%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration%20said%20was%20driven%20by%20Moscow's%20violation%20of%20the%20treaty%20with%20its%20SSC-8%2F9M729%2C%20has%20opened%20new%20doors%20for%20the%20US%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20GAO%20report%2C%20the%20office%20noted%20that%20the%20effort%20underway%20for%20the%20MRC%20has%20%26quot%3Breflected%20several%20attributes%20of%20an%20iterative%20product%20development%20approach%20as%20it%20established%20a%20business%20case%20with%20flexible%20requirements%20focused%20on%20a%20minimum%20viable%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20adapting%20new%20capabilities%20and%20requesting%20user%20feedback%20on%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIterative%2C%20or%20staged%2C%20development%20with%20key%20soldier%20feedback%20has%20been%20of%20growing%20interest%20for%20US%20Army's%20transformation%20and%20innovation%20projects.%20The%20Army%20has%20called%20these%20soldier%20touchpoints%2C%20but%20there%20are%20many%20names%20for%20this%20process%20within%20the%20military.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-special-operations-forces-has-answer-to-militarys-weapons-problem-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20special%20operations%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20been%20really%20involved%20in%20this%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20work%20in%20the%20field%20has%20also%20been%20seen%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20where%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20are%20often%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20and%20providing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-operator-texts-facetimes-with-makers-makes-better-weapons-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efeedback%20to%20weapons%20makers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fueling%20rapid%20growth%20in%20experimental%20and%20emerging%20combat%20technologies.%20The%20Army's%20first%20iteration%20of%20the%20Mid-Range%20Capability%20experienced%20that%20during%20the%20Philippines%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitary%20leaders%20have%20said%20that%20companies%20should%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-companies-without-ukraine-battlefield-presence-give-up-uk-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etesting%20their%20tech%20on%20the%20front%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Short%20of%20that%2C%20they'd%20ideally%20be%20getting%20their%20systems%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20deployed%20troops%20in%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-reworked-new-missile-on-ground-key-pacific-ally-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751398461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22