%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorkfed.org%2Fresearch%2Fcollege-labor-market%23--%3Aexplore%3Aoutcomes-by-major%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzed%20the%20unemployment%20rates%20of%20recent%20college%20graduates%2C%20defined%20as%2022-%20to%2027-year-olds%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20higher%2C%20by%20major.%20The%20analysis%20used%20data%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%202023%20American%20Community%20Survey%20covering%2073%20majors%20and%20subject%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-eight%20majors%20had%20unemployment%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erates%20above%20the%20overall%203.6%25%20rate%20for%20recent%20grads.%20The%20kinds%20of%20majors%20with%20the%20highest%20unemployment%20rates%20were%20mixed%2C%20with%20several%20related%20to%20arts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-engineer-advice-students-internships-first-second-year-programs-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechnology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20science.%20Recent%20anthropology%20graduates%20had%20a%20rate%20of%209.4%25%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%2C%20followed%20by%20physics%20at%207.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FkOC7J%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Unemployment%20rate%20in%202023%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20computer%20engineering%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomputer-science-major-panic-masters-degree-graduate-school-job-market-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomputer%20science%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20had%20high%20unemployment.%20Still%2C%20employed%20graduates%20in%20the%20two%20computer-related%20majors%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworking%20in%20jobs%20that%20typically%20require%20a%20degree%2C%20especially%20compared%20to%20anthropology.%20They%20also%20tied%20with%20the%20highest%20median%20wage%20for%20early-career%20graduates%2C%20alongside%20chemical%20engineering%2C%20at%20%2480%2C000%2C%20and%20had%20six-figure%20medians%20for%20mid-career%20graduates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Zhao%2C%20lead%20economist%20at%20job%20platform%20Glassdoor%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20computer%20science%20and%20engineering%20are%20still%20appealing%20because%20of%20the%20high%20pay%20they%20could%20lead%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20higher%20unemployment%20rate%20but%20the%20lower%20underemployment%20rate%2C%20new%20grads%20in%20computing%20fields%20are%20likely%20holding%20out%2C%20waiting%20for%20that%20first%20job%20in%20the%20field%2C%20because%20they%20know%20how%20rewarding%20it%20can%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaison%20Abel%2C%20the%20head%20of%20microeconomics%20at%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20tech%20sector%20tends%20to%20hire%20many%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-college-grad-redefine-success-first-full-time-job-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20showed%20some%20overall%20weakness%20from%20mid-2022%20into%20the%20following%20year%2C%20after%20higher%20demand%20for%20workers%20following%20the%20pandemic%20recession.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20tech%20sector%20does%20tend%20to%20hire%20grads%20who%20studied%20physics%2C%20computer%20engineering%2C%20and%20computer%20science%20%E2%80%94%20three%20of%20the%20majors%20with%20relatively%20high%20unemployment%20rates%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbel%20said%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20chunk%20of%20the%20elevated%20unemployment%20at%20that%20time%20for%20recent%20grads%26quot%3B%20in%20those%20three%20majors%20was%20because%20they%20%26quot%3Bjust%20happened%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20economy%20that%20was%20experiencing%20a%20bit%20more%20weakness%20than%20other%20parts%2C%20even%20though%20the%20economy%20overall%20was%20still%20quite%20strong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20outlook%20for%20science%20graduates%20was%20mixed.%20While%20physics%20and%20chemistry%20both%20had%20relatively%20high%20unemployment%20rates%2C%20earth%20sciences%20had%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20of%20just%201.5%25.%20Biology%20had%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20of%203%25%2C%20below%20the%20overall%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20pure%20sciences%2C%20the%20types%20of%20jobs%20you%20can%20get%20do%20tend%20to%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20constrained%20than%20some%20of%20the%20engineering%20fields%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20science%20jobs%20tend%20to%20rely%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientist-federal-funds-held-trump-fire-employees-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20unemployment%20data%20is%20about%202023%2C%20Zhao%20said%20the%20dependence%20on%20federal%20funding%20is%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%20a%20concern%20moving%20forward%2C%20as%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20pulled%20back%20on%20funding%20for%20research%20and%20science.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b07d13de-0ad5-4aed-8afc-0c4dc876317b%5C%22%3EThe%20job%20market%20can%20%3Cstrong%3Estill%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebe%20hard%20for%20new%20job%20seekers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20job%20openings%20have%20slowed%20dramatically%20since%20the%20post-pandemic%20boom%2C%20and%20there%20are%20fewer%20openings%20per%20unemployed%20person.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20recent%2022-to-27-year-old%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharts-gen-z-college-grads-job-market-hiring-unemployment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20higher%20climbed%20to%205.8%25%20in%20March%2C%20widening%20the%20gap%20with%20the%20overall%20unemployment%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20exactly%20how%20the%20individual%20majors%20will%20shake%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Abel%20said%20about%20today's%20job%20market.%20%26quot%3BAll%20else%20equal%2C%20if%20you've%20just%20got%20a%20cooler%20job%20market%20with%20less%20hiring%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20equate%20to%20a%20higher%20unemployment%20rate%2C%20especially%20for%20recent%20grads%2C%20because%20recent%20grads%20are%20really%20on%20the%20margin%20of%20the%20labor%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20graduates%20could%20be%20having%20a%20tougher%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-youre-not-getting-hired-job-interview-resume-advice-tips-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20depending%20on%20where%20they're%20applying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20job%20market%20in%20tech%20has%20been%20soft%20for%20entry-level%20workers%2C%20as%20many%20tech%20companies%20have%20slowed%20down%20hiring%20or%20even%20turned%20to%20layoffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20postings%20in%20the%20software%20development%20sector%20on%20the%20job%20search%20platform%20Indeed%20have%20recently%20been%20growing%2C%20but%20they%20are%20still%20far%20below%20the%20opportunities%20during%202022%20and%20even%20pre-pandemic%20February%202020.%20Job%20postings%20for%20the%20scientific%20research%20and%20development%20sector%20have%20also%20slowed%20from%20their%20March%202022%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao's%20advice%20for%20new%20graduates%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20is%20to%20connect%20with%20their%20networks%2C%20such%20as%20alumni%20and%20family%2C%20and%20research%20who%20is%20still%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%20with%20which%20career%20path%20you%20can%20pursue%20because%20entry-level%20workers%2C%20usually%2C%20the%20skills%20are%20more%20generalizable%20across%20industries%20or%20across%20occupations%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20college%20graduate%20who%20is%20job%20searching%2C%20or%20did%20you%20get%20a%20job%20without%20a%20college%20degree%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20your%20story%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-college-majors-anthropology-physics-computer-engineering-jobs-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751394073000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6862889985e81483682d0674%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-college-majors-anthropology-physics-computer-engineering-jobs-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Recent%20college%20graduates%20in%20about%20a%20dozen%20college%20majors%20had%20unemployment%20rates%20above%205%25%20in%202023%2C%20an%20analysis%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%20showed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-college-majors-anthropology-physics-computer-engineering-jobs-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22See%20inside%20Eagle's%20Nest%2C%20the%2042-acre%20New%20York%20Vanderbilt%20estate%20where%20a%20Gilded%20Age%20heir%20built%20his%20sprawling%20mansion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225128%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22courtyard%20vanderbilt%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686420253d5881a51c1c7623%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%2