here%20are%20limits%2C%20however%2C%20to%20what%20the%20companies%20consider%20%26quot%3BIP.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Microsoft%20gets%20access%20to%20important%20aspects%20of%20OpenAI's%20models%2C%20like%20model%20weights%20that%20help%20determine%20AI%20outputs%20and%20inference%20codes%20that%20instruct%20the%20models%20on%20how%20to%20use%20data%2C%20the%20people%20said.%20Some%20things%20are%20excluded%20from%20what%20the%20companies%20consider%20IP%2C%20like%20product%20and%20user%20interface%20information%2C%20they%20said%2C%20and%20the%20point%20at%20which%20OpenAI%20must%20share%20any%20technology%20is%20up%20to%20interpretation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20with%20knowledge%20of%20OpenAI's%20operations%20said%20the%20company%20doesn't%20have%20to%20share%20what%20it's%20developing%20until%20it's%20finished%2C%20which%20can%20be%20subjective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20make%20sure%20you%20share%20something%20with%20Microsoft%20as%20late%20as%20possible%2C%20so%20they%20can%20still%20simultaneously%20announce%2C%20but%20make%20it%20really%20difficult%20to%20build%20the%20same%20product%20on%20top%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20having%20access%20to%20the%20IP%20isn't%20the%20same%20as%20knowing%20how%20to%20use%20it.%20This%20has%20been%20harder%20than%20expected%2C%20several%20people%20told%20BI.%20OpenAI%20has%20grown%20frustrated%20with%20Microsoft's%20request%20to%20spell%20out%20the%20technology%20to%20its%20employees%2C%20people%20with%20knowledge%20of%20both%20companies%20said.%20Sometimes%2C%20Microsoft%20doesn't%20know%20what%20questions%20to%20ask%20of%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hired-inflection-team-amid-board-concerns-about-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eformed%20a%20new%20AI%20organization%20two%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hired%20Mustafa%20Suleyman%2C%20the%20former%20Inflection%20CEO%20who%20cofounded%20the%20AI%20pioneer%20DeepMind%2C%20to%20run%20it.%20The%20hiring%20was%20meant%20as%20a%20hedge%20against%20OpenAI%2C%20after%20Nadella%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hired-inflection-team-amid-board-concerns-about-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%20pressure%20from%20Microsoft's%20board%20to%20diversify%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0following%20instability%20at%20its%20partner%20startup%20and%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-shock-firing-from-openai-just-became-bigger-mystery-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eouster.%3C%2Fa%3E%20However%2C%20little%20has%20come%20of%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20replacing%20Microsoft's%20need%20for%20its%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuleyman%20has%20completely%20rebuilt%20Microsoft's%20Copilot%20app.%20That%20effort%20has%20yet%20to%20achieve%20much%20growth%20for%20Copilot.%20His%20team%20is%20focused%20on%20building%20smaller%20models%20and%20has%20seen%20success%20with%20post-training%20existing%20models%20for%20new%20purposes%2C%20one%20of%20the%20people%20said.%20Overall%2C%20Microsoft%20isn't%20trying%20to%20build%20frontier%20models%20like%20those%20that%20would%20compete%20with%20GPT%2C%20and%20is%20instead%20putting%20resources%20toward%20OpenAI%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228059b6b5-46ae-4da4-8211-095c15095504%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20is%20less%20worried%20about%20AGI%2C%20antitrust%2C%20Windsurf%2C%20or%20SoftBank%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20points%20of%20contention%20that%20have%20made%20recent%20headlines%20are%20of%20less%20concern%20to%20Microsoft%2C%20the%20people%20with%20knowledge%20of%20Microsoft's%20position%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncluded%20in%20the%20agreement%20is%20a%20clause%20that%20would%20allow%20OpenAI%20to%20declare%20what's%20called%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20or%20%26quot%3BAGI%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20cut%20off%20Microsoft's%20access%20to%20OpenAI's%20IP%20and%20profits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Four-structure%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20defines%20AGI%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20highly%20autonomous%20system%20that%20outperforms%20humans%20at%20most%20economically%20valuable%20works.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20OpenAI%20could%20declare%20AGI%2C%20the%20concept%20is%20so%20open%20to%20interpretation%20that%20Microsoft%20could%20sue%20and%20easily%20tie%20the%20company%20up%20in%20a%20legal%20battle%20for%20years%2C%20the%20people%20said.%20There's%20another%20version%20of%20the%20clause%2C%20%26quot%3Bsufficient%20AGI%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20OpenAI%20could%20declare%20when%20it%20builds%20a%20technology%20capable%20of%20achieving%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20profits%2C%20but%20Microsoft%20has%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20apparent%20sticking%20point%20in%20the%20negotiations%20has%20centered%20on%20OpenAI's%20desire%20to%20acquire%20AI%20coding%20assistant%20startup%20Windsurf.%20Under%20the%20current%20agreement%2C%20that%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-internal-memo-using-ai-no-longer-optional-github-copilot-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egive%20Microsoft%20access%20to%20Windsurf's%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Microsoft%20has%20said%20it%20would%20agree%20to%20the%20acquisition%2C%20but%20Windsurf's%20CEO%20doesn't%20want%20the%20company's%20technology%20to%20be%20shared%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20one%20of%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20GitHub%20Copilot%20faces%20increasing%20competition%20from%20other%20AI%20coding%20assistants%2C%20access%20to%20Windsurf's%20technology%20is%20not%20a%20big%20desire%20for%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20the%20company%20might%20consider%20a%20carve-out%20of%20Windsurf%20IP%20in%20a%20new%20deal%2C%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20executives%20have%20%3Ca%20href