%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-meditate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeditation%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20really%20important.%20I%20do%20not%20do%20it%20nearly%20enough%2C%20but%20I%20try%20to%20do%20it%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20That%20has%20helped%20me%20a%20lot%20just%20with%20clarity%2C%20purpose%2C%20and%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20three%20kids%20and%20obviously%20a%20house%20full%20of%20pets%2C%20of%20course%2C%20there's%20stress%2C%20and%20things%20are%20going%20to%20come%20up.%20But%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%2C%20give%20yourself%20even%20just%20an%20hour%20a%20day%20to%20approach%20everything%20calmly%2C%20has%20made%20a%20huge%20difference%20to%20my%20health%2C%20my%20mentality%2C%20and%20even%20just%20ensuring%20I%20get%20a%20better%20night's%20sleep%2C%20which%20then%20ensures%20that%20my%20body%20and%20mind%20and%20everything%20functions%20better%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20know%20you've%20spoken%20about%20perimenopause%20before.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224132%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Katherine%20Heigl%20and%20husband%20Josh%20Kelley%20in%20April%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68628af93d5881a51c1c57fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKatherine%20Heigl%20and%20husband%20Josh%20Kelley%20in%20April%202017.%3Cp%3EGregg%20DeGuire%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYeah.%20Whoever%20designed%20it%20so%20that%20women%20would%20be%20going%20through%20perimenopause%20while%20raising%20teenagers%20should%20be%20sent%20a%20strongly%20worded%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20difficult.%20Their%20hormones%20are%20all%20over%20the%20place%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20adapt%20and%20get%20used%20to%20their%20new%20bodies%20and%20their%20new%20ways%20of%20thinking%2C%20and%20I%20am%20too.%20So%20the%20only%20thing%20I%20can%20do%20is%20look%20at%20them%20and%20go%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20at%20least%20we're%20in%20it%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20started%20researching%20something%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Feight-sleep-pod-4-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEight%20Sleep%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20it%20goes%20over%20your%20mattress%20to%20keep%20the%20bed%20cool%20at%20night.%20The%20number%20of%20nights%20that%20I%20wake%20up%20so%20hot%20and%20drenched%20in%20sweat.%20The%20good%20news%20is%20that%20I%20live%20in%20Utah%2C%20and%20nine%20months%20out%20of%20the%20year%2C%20it's%20freezing%2C%20so%20I%20can%20just%20step%20outside%20and%20cool%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerimenopause%20is%20like%20having%20to%20relearn%20your%20whole%20system%20and%20body%20again.%20I%20feel%20like%20it%20happens%20almost%20every%2010%20years.%20In%20my%2020s%2C%20my%20hormones%20were%20crazy%20and%20tumultuous%2C%20and%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20figure%20myself%20out.%20And%20then%20I%20had%2010%20years%20in%20my%2030s%20where%20I%20had%20a%20good%20handle%20on%20it%20all%2C%20and%20then%20it%20all%20started%20shifting%20and%20changing%20again%20at%20about%2040.%20Great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJust%20endless%20changes%2C%20that's%20exhausting.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGet%20used%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20wind%20down%20to%20give%20yourself%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20a%20good%20sleep%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20nights%20where%20we'll%20watch%20a%20show%20%E2%80%94%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20gotten%20really%20into%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-succession-gets-right-about-real-life-billionaires-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESuccession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20I%20prefer%20to%20read%20for%20an%20hour%20before%20actually%20putting%20my%20head%20on%20the%20pillow.%3C%2